<div id="review_127646663" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/127646663" />
    <a title="Janne Järvinen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4418742-janne-j-rvinen"><img alt="Janne Järvinen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1287105275p2/4418742.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/127646663?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janne Järvinen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janne Järvinen" href="/user/show/4418742-janne-j-rvinen">Janne Järvinen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780330320962" href="/book/show/872934.Nightfall">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4418742-janne-j-rvinen?shelf=scifi">scifi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer127646663" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18163596197093658940">Nightfall isn&apos;t that bad. The plot advances at a nice pace. It all breaks down in the end, though. At points I was close to giving Nightfall three stars. The bad delivery of the ending, and the overall pulpiness of the story, are what drop the rating.<br/><br/>The story is fun, but has a full time job holding itself together just on the surface level. This leaves no room for any depth.<br/><br/>The final resolution of the story is not that bad in itself, but the way it is told is anti-climactic. Some people say the</span>
  <span id="freeText18163596197093658940" style="display:none">Nightfall isn't that bad. The plot advances at a nice pace. It all breaks down in the end, though. At points I was close to giving Nightfall three stars. The bad delivery of the ending, and the overall pulpiness of the story, are what drop the rating.<br /><br />The story is fun, but has a full time job holding itself together just on the surface level. This leaves no room for any depth.<br /><br />The final resolution of the story is not that bad in itself, but the way it is told is anti-climactic. Some people say there is not enough here for a novel, that Asimov should've kept it a short story, but I disgree. If anything, the book should have been longer, to let the ending play out in a more dramatic fashion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18163596197093658940" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
