              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/735627-clackamas?shelf=apocalyptic-fiction-dystopias">apocalyptic-fiction-dystopias</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/735627-clackamas?shelf=all-time-loves">all-time-loves</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer12328691" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16857702297612097098">***Upgraded this book to an all time love. I keep rereading it and love it every time. Originally read 10/1994. Reread every year or so since then***<br/><br/>I love this kind of book. It introduces us to a world and characters before the disaster, follows them through it, and shows us the aftermath. It&apos;s very character-driven. It&apos;s surprising to read a book with so many characters that are being followed, and yet have them all fleshed out and three-dimensional so that you can actually care about them. </span>
  <span id="freeText16857702297612097098" style="display:none">***Upgraded this book to an all time love. I keep rereading it and love it every time. Originally read 10/1994. Reread every year or so since then***<br /><br />I love this kind of book. It introduces us to a world and characters before the disaster, follows them through it, and shows us the aftermath. It's very character-driven. It's surprising to read a book with so many characters that are being followed, and yet have them all fleshed out and three-dimensional so that you can actually care about them. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16857702297612097098" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
